# Legacy HTML In Inertia Pages

Legacy CMS/admin content may be stored as raw HTML and rendered in Vue with `v-html`.

- Server owns the data: load HTML in Rails and pass it as an Inertia prop.
- Sanitize HTML on the server before sending it to Vue.
- Remove `script` and `style` nodes before `helpers.sanitize`; Rails sanitize removes tags but can preserve script text.
- Keep Vue components as renderers. Do not fetch page HTML client-side.
- When legacy HTML contains `<br>`, do not assume whether to keep, normalize, or remove them. Ask the user what behavior they want for that content, because `<br>` may be intentional editorial formatting or legacy spacing noise.
- Never globally hide `<br>` with CSS unless the user explicitly chooses that behavior.
- Localize accessibility labels (`aria-label`, screen-reader text) via Rails props or `locale_messages`, not hardcoded strings.
